    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Spring Rolls are crispy, golden-fried rolls stuffed with a flavorful mix of saut√©ed vegetables. These crunchy delights are perfect as starters or evening snacks.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>10 spring roll sheets</li>
        <li>1 cup cabbage (shredded)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup carrots (julienned)</li>
        <li>1/2 cup capsicum (sliced)</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp black pepper</li>
        <li>1 tbsp soy sauce</li>
        <li>1 tsp vinegar</li>
        <li>1 tsp cornflour + water (for sealing)</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>Oil for frying</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan and stir-fry all vegetables for 2‚Äì3 minutes.</li>
        <li>Add soy sauce, vinegar, pepper, and salt. Mix and let it cool.</li>
        <li>Place filling on a spring roll sheet, fold, and seal edges using cornflour paste.</li>
        <li>Repeat for all rolls.</li>
        <li>Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown and crispy.</li>
        <li>Serve hot with sweet chili sauce or ketchup.</li>
    </ol>
